Sterling Ingwers is a UC Davis alumni, she majored in Environmental Science and Policy Environmental Science.  She also majored in Mechanical Engineering at UC San Diego.  She previously was a member of Alpha Phi and president of Foundation for the Defense of Democracies at UC Davis FDD. She was also the Capitol ViceChair for California College Republicans.

Disenchanted by the recent administration and global affairs, she is now disassociated with the Republican party.  Sterling is currently a grass roots environmental activist and participant in various Buddhist meditation groups.  Sterling now specializes in renewable energy development at an engineering firm in Sacramento.

